Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The text today is taken \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.99,0:00:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,from The Watchtower of 2016, January, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.42,0:00:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and the theme \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.43,0:00:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be Compelled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.43,0:00:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by God’s ‘Indescribable Free Gift.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.13,0:00:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this Memorial season \Nreally does move us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.87,0:00:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to contemplate what Jehovah has done for us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.77,0:00:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and we should be compelled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.81,0:00:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The Insight volume has \Na very interesting article \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.71,0:00:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,on this matter of forgiveness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And in one of the statements it mentions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.55,0:00:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that “the Hebrew verb sa·lachʹ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“[for] (forgive) \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.32,0:00:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is used only with regard \Nto [Jehovah’s] pardoning a sinner.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.33,0:00:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s never used in connection \Nwith a human forgiving a human. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the extent of \Nand reasons for Jehovah’s forgiveness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.21,0:00:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,really are unmatchable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.41,0:01:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what should we be compelled to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.25,0:01:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s reflect \Non the illustration that Jesus gave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in Matthew chapter 18, \Nand if you turn there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.49,0:01:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll recall that in verse 21 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.02,0:01:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter had asked: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.16,0:01:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Lord, how many times am I to forgive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.76,0:01:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‘my brother if he sins against me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.53,0:01:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to seven times?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.63,0:01:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what was wrong with that question? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.70,0:01:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Peter had been influenced \Nby a hard-hearted spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.71,0:01:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that was prevalent in those days, \Nand in some instances even today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.38,0:01:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do we mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.38,0:01:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Peter measured forgiveness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.72,0:01:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was common among the Pharisees. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.86,0:01:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus went on to say what in verse 22? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.50,0:01:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We know it very well: \N“I say to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.96,0:01:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not up to seven times, \Nbut up to 77 times.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.00,0:02:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in connection \Nwith divine forgiveness he\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jesus—\Nresponds in a way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.77,0:02:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that helps us to see the contrast \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.34,0:02:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the human understanding \Nof forgiveness and God’s. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.65,0:02:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what he says in verse 23: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.85,0:02:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“That is why the Kingdom of the heavens \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.32,0:02:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“may be likened \Nto a king who wanted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.32,0:02:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to settle accounts with his slaves.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now notice, \Nthe king wanted to settle accounts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.06,0:02:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t the slaves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.43,0:02:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The slaves had built up a debt with the king, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.64,0:02:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and justice called for the king \Nto handle matters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.64,0:02:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—balance the books, as it were. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.04,0:02:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, he found one slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.85,0:02:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“who owed him 10,000 talents” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.92,0:02:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—40 million dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.32,0:02:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a lot of money.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.92,0:02:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.29,0:02:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,—if we think about that illustration—\Nis telling us something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He has given those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.90,0:03:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that are his slaves\N—us—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of leeway. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He has forgiven us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.51,0:03:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of times, \Nso often that we are not aware, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.85,0:03:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,really, of the many sins \Nwe commit against Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, going back to the illustration, \Nverse 26. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This slave begs \Nbecause he can’t afford to pay, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and he says to the master: \N‘Be patient with me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.13,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’ll pay everything I owe you.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.06,0:03:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how in the world could he do that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.17,0:03:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a slave. \NHow could he pay back 40 million dollars? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.97,0:03:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the master knew that there \Nwas no way he could pay this back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.78,0:03:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now, putting the illustration \Nin today’s terms, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.75,0:03:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the average yearly wage \Nfor the United States\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.05,0:03:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—I googled this—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in 2014 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.15,0:04:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,was almost 52,000 dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s just averaging out everybody. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.66,0:04:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a lot of people \Nwho don’t make that much, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.66,0:04:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and many who make more than that, \Nbut the average was 52,000 dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.57,0:04:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if the 10,000 talents \Nequaled 40 million dollars, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it would take a man 770 years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.64,0:04:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to pay off that debt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.64,0:04:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if he gave everything that he made \Nto pay off the debt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.75,0:04:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the master knew, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.75,0:04:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,‘This slave, he can’t—\Nhe can’t pay me.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.99,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So verse 27 says: \N“Moved with pity at this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.99,0:04:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the master of that slave \Nlet him off and canceled his debt.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.93,0:04:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, what a relief that would be. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But the slave \Nshould have recognized something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.07,0:04:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He could never be \Nin the same position as the master. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t have the resources. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.94,0:04:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor could anyone possibly owe him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.95,0:05:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what he owed the master. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.15,0:05:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if he had captured the spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.65,0:05:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of forgiveness shown to him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.02,0:05:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there would hardly be any debt owed to him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.19,0:05:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that he couldn’t tolerate or even forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But in verse 28, look at his attitude: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“That slave went out \Nand found one of his fellow slaves, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.84,0:05:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[on the same plane as him] \Nwho owed him 100 denarii [70 dollars].” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.11,0:05:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now notice, \Nhe “went out and found” that slave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So rather than looking to overlook \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.55,0:05:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the debts of those who were indebted to him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.49,0:05:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he was looking for those who owed him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.06,0:05:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we’re going to read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.60,0:05:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 29, 30, 32, 33, and 35. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.30,0:05:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.30,0:05:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“So his fellow slave fell down \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.71,0:06:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“and began to beg him, saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.11,0:06:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Be patient with me, \Nand I will pay you back.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, he was not willing.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s stop there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that this slave \Nthat owed him could pay him back? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.19,0:06:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was possible he could work it out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.86,0:06:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,within his resources\N—70 dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.03,0:06:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what was the reaction? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.20,0:06:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The account says: \N“He went and had him thrown into prison \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.20,0:06:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,until he could pay back what he owed.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, how petty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.58,0:06:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 32: “Then [the] master \Nsummoned him and said to him: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Wicked slave, I canceled \Nall that debt for you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.22,0:06:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘when you pleaded with me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.22,0:06:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘[that debt that you \Ncould never have paid off]. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Should you not also have shown mercy \Nto your fellow slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.56,0:06:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘[that slave who possibly \Ncould have paid it off the same] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.50,0:06:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as I showed mercy to you?’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.77,0:07:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the clincher, \Nverse 35, Jesus’ point: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.37,0:07:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“My heavenly Father will also deal with you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“[that’s me, and that’s you] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the same way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.95,0:07:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if each of you \Ndoes not forgive your brother.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by rote, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not by formula, \Nbut ‘from our heart.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.39,0:07:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the king, as we said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.39,0:07:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,forgave the debt of 40 million dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.30,0:07:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That slave was unwilling \Nto forgive his fellow slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.27,0:07:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for the amount of 70 dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.10,0:07:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is a big Forgiver, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.94,0:07:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and we thank him for that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.94,0:07:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Last evening helped us to see how big. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, grasping the depth \Nof our indebtedness to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.85,0:07:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the depth of his forgiveness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.39,0:07:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,should compel us to constantly work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at having a forgiving spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.46,0:08:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Insight volume says that in the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“the Hebrew word na·saʼʹ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.97,0:08:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“may denote the pardon, or forgiveness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.64,0:08:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,extended by God or by humans.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.57,0:08:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we stated originally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.57,0:08:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“sa·lachʹ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.58,0:08:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“is used exclusively \N[for] God’s forgiveness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.11,0:08:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the act by which [a] sinner \Nis restored to divine favor.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now remember, our forgiveness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,can’t begin to match Jehovah’s. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.26,0:08:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So there’s nothing that any human \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.82,0:08:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can do to us that matches what we\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.86,0:08:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—born in sin, alienated from God, \Ninclined to do wrong—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.43,0:08:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,have done to offend Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.90,0:08:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—as we discussed yesterday, \Nlast evening, and we’re reminded of—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.51,0:08:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,God recommends his own love to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.08,0:08:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and that “while we were yet sinners” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.15,0:08:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,he had his Son die for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.45,0:09:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to quote to you \NThe Watchtower of October 15, 1999, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,page 13\N—October 15, 1999. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.09,0:09:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The article is “Forgive From Your Heart.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.83,0:09:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It says this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.83,0:09:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“You should see in God’s willingness \Nto forgive a pattern \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.57,0:09:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“as to how you ought to treat other humans. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.91,0:09:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Paul focused on this, writing: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.17,0:09:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Become kind to one another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,tenderly compassionate, freely forgiving.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.95,0:09:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Not like an accountant keeping track, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.32,0:09:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but “freely forgiving one another \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.82,0:09:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,just as God also by Christ \Nfreely forgave you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.16,0:09:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then The Watchtower says this: \N“Do you see the link? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah God forgave you, [that’s me]\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.73,0:09:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“so\N—Paul forcefully reasons—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.50,0:09:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“you need to imitate [God] Him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and be ‘tenderly compassionate, \Nfreely forgiving’ of others.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then The Watchtower asked \Nsome penetrating questions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.88,0:09:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It said: “Ask yourself, \N‘Am I [really] doing that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.85,0:10:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘If it is not [in] my nature, \Nam I working in that direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,really striving to imitate God \Nin being forgiving?’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.96,0:10:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we might say: \N‘Well, I’m forgiving. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgive a lot of people.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.49,0:10:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Proof? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 17:9: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.97,0:10:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whoever forgives a transgression seeks love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one who keeps harping \Non a matter separates close friends.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.57,0:10:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If we keep talking about \Nwhat somebody has done to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.31,0:10:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we haven’t forgiven in the heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.78,0:10:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah doesn’t do that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.11,0:10:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So forgiving others for personal offenses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.55,0:10:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of the number of times involved, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.58,0:10:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is a Christian requirement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.89,0:10:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s forgiveness is not extended \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,toward those who refuse to forgive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.59,0:10:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what Jesus said: \N“Forgive us our debts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as we also have forgiven our debtors.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.73,0:10:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a beautiful God we have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.17,0:10:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,His action and that of his Son compels us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:10:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to be freely forgiving. \N
